    "content_hash": "87af981907f023cd",
    "department": "Marketing",
    "description": "ABOUT RAMP\n\nRamp is building the smart infrastructure for finance teams, embedded in the transaction flow of every dollar a business spends. We automate how over $100B in annualized spend flows in and out of 50,000+ companies: authorizing payments, flagging risk, categorizing spend, and closing books.\n\nThe problems are high-stakes, data-dense, and unforgiving.\n\nWe hire people with high agency and high urgency. We look for slope over intercept. We care less about where you trained and more about what you’ve built. At Ramp, everyone is a builder who owns problems end to end and makes consequential decisions that shape the outcome.\n\nThe median Ramp customer saves 5% and grows revenue 16% in their first year – far in excess of businesses operating without Ramp. We believe every ambitious company deserves the same.\n\nIf you want to build systems that directly shape how companies move and manage billions, Ramp is the place to do it.\n\n\nABOUT THE ROLE\n\nInfluencer marketing is one of Ramp’s highest-ROI growth channels, driving some of our most efficient and scalable SQL impact across performance, product launches, and brand moments. This role owns the end-to-end influencer motion and scales it from a high-performing but under-resourced program into a durable, company-wide growth engine.\n\nYou’ll partner closely with Performance Marketing while supporting cross-functional initiatives across Product, Sales, Brand, and GTM. This is a hands-on role with real budget ownership, high creative judgment, and clear business impact.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL DO\n\n - Own Ramp’s influencer program end-to-end, from strategy through execution and optimization\n\n - Partner with Performance, Data, Finance and Brand to scope goals, budgets, and timelines for influencer campaigns\n\n - Source, evaluate, and build shortlists of creators aligned to audience, product, and channel goals\n\n - Lead outreach, briefing, contracting, and negotiation (rates, deliverables, usage rights, exclusivity)\n\n - Review and guide creative to ensure strong messaging, performance signal, and brand alignment\n\n - Coordinate posting, collaboration tags, and distribution across Ramp-owned channels\n\n - Track performance, synthesize learnings, and continuously improve creator selection and briefs\n\n\nWHAT YOU NEED\n\n - 4-7+ years of experience in influencer marketing, creator partnerships, or performance creative roles\n\n - Direct experience running paid influencer campaigns tied to performance or revenue outcomes\n\n - Strong creator taste and judgment beyond follower count or surface-level metrics\n\n - Comfort negotiating contracts, usage rights, and paid amplification terms\n\n - Ability to manage multiple campaigns and stakeholders simultaneously without losing quality\n\n - Clear written and verbal communication, especially when briefing creators and aligning XFN teams\n\n\nNICE-TO-HAVES\n\n - Experience at a high-growth startup or performance-driven marketing org\n\n - Familiarity with Meta, TikTok, YouTube, and LinkedIn paid ecosystems\n\n - Experience supporting product launches, GTM motions, or sales-led initiatives\n\n - Comfort working with Legal and Procurement on creator contracts\n\n\nBENEFITS (FOR U.S.-BASED FULL-TIME EMPLOYEES)\n\n - 100% medical, dental \u0026 vision insurance coverage for you\n   \n   - Partially covered for your dependents\n   \n   - One Medical annual membership\n\n - 401k (including employer match on contributions made while employed by Ramp)\n\n - Flexible PTO\n\n - Fertility HRA (up to $10,000 per year)\n\n - Parental Leave\n\n - Unlimited AI token usage\n\n - Pet insurance\n\n - Centralized home-office equipment ordering for all employees\n\n - Health and Wellness stipend\n\n - In-office perks: lunch, snacks, drinks, and more\n\n - Budget for intra-office travel\n\n - Relocation support to NYC or SF (as needed)\n\n\nREFERRAL INSTRUCTIONS\n\nIf you are being referred for the role, please contact that person to apply on your behalf.\n\n\nOTHER NOTICES\n\nPursuant to the San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance, we will consider for employment qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records.\n\nBeware of recruiting scams: Ramp will only contact you through official @Ramp.com http://Ramp.com email addresses and will never ask for payment or sensitive personal information during the hiring process.\n\nRamp Applicant Privacy Notice https://ramp.com/legal/applicant-privacy-notice",
